channel.title: What program does this icon go to?
channel.description:
What program does this icon go to?
[URL=http://imageshack.us][IMG]http://img382.imageshack.us/img382/3193/untitleduk1.png[/img][/URL]
The program wont let me keep any of the theme or desktop settings when i logoff so can someone tell me what program it is??
[font=Verdana]/Subject fixed -kmb[/font]

item.title: What program does this icon go to?
item.dc:creator: @deoxys505 deoxys505
item.description:
@deoxys505 wrote:

ok, first off, i have gone to task manager and found out what the tray icon task is called. its called CStray.exe.

On another topic

why not hover over it? tada

when i hover over it and right click it, nothing appears. when i double click, all that pops up is a box that tells you to enter the password.

[quote=“Rictoo, post:3, topic:70190”]Check your taskmgr for wierd processes, and get out of them one by one (after you get out of each, hover your mouse over the icon in the system tray), until the icon goes away. Then go to start>run>msconfig>Startup and untick the process the icon belongs to.[/quote]the msconfig is disabled…so i cant disable the program from starting up…

P.S. i know that program is the one that causes me to keep my crappy theme because the girl that sits next to me had that program disabled, and she could keep her desktop and theme…
